\p 
\v 3 \w Jephthah|strong="H3316"\w* \w ran|strong="H1272"\w* \w away|strong="H1272"\w* \w from|strong="H3318"\w* \w his|strong="H6440"\w* brothers \w and|strong="H6440"\w* \w went|strong="H3318"\w* \w to|strong="H3318"\w* \w live|strong="H3427"\w* \w in|strong="H3427"\w* \w the|strong="H6440"\w* \w land|strong="H6440"\w* \w of|strong="H3427"\w* \w Tob|strong="H2897"\w*. \w A|strong="H3068"\w* gang \w of|strong="H3427"\w* trouble-makers \w joined|strong="H3950"\w* \w him|strong="H6440"\w* \w and|strong="H6440"\w* \w he|strong="H3318"\w* \w led|strong="H3318"\w* \w them|strong="H6440"\w* \w out|strong="H3318"\w* \w on|strong="H3427"\w* raids.\f + \fr 11:3 \ft The Hebrew simply says, “they went out with him,” however the context indicates they were a band of mercenaries.\f*
